Following Rob&#39;s [suggestion][1], just a few steps need to be taken when using this via Maven and [openapi-generator-maven-plugin][2]

1. Create a new maven module.

2. Create a class for the code generator extending [JavaJAXRSSpecServerCodegen][3]. This adds `&quot;StreamingOutput&quot;` as type mapping for `&quot;file&quot;` and `&quot;binary&quot;` (only `&quot;file&quot;` was sufficient for my spec) and also adds an import for `javax.ws.rs.core.StreamingOutput`
    ```java
    public class JaxrsSpecStreamingOutputGenerator extends JavaJAXRSSpecServerCodegen {

        protected static final String GENERATOR_NAME = &quot;jaxrs-spec-streamingoutput&quot;;

        @Override
        public String getName() {
            return GENERATOR_NAME;
        }

        @Override
        public String getHelp() {
            return super.getHelp() + &quot;\njava.io.File is replaced with &quot; + StreamingOutput.class.getName();
        }

        public JaxrsSpecStreamingOutputGenerator() {
            String shortName = &quot;StreamingOutput&quot;;

            importMapping.put(shortName, StreamingOutput.class.getName());
            // use &#39;StreamingOutput&#39; for &#39;binary&#39; and &#39;file&#39;
            typeMapping.put(&quot;binary&quot;, shortName);
            typeMapping.put(&quot;file&quot;, shortName);
        }
    }
    ```

    This code generator is identified by `jaxrs-spec-streamingoutput`

3. Add `META-INF/services/org.openapitools.codegen.CodegenConfig` with the following contents:
    ```
    ${package}.JaxrsSpecStreamingOutputGenerator
    ```
    (replace `${package}` with the actual package name)

---

Alternatively, the maven module and all necessary files generated using the OpenAPI Generator CLI [meta][4] command.

```shell
java -jar openapi-generator-cli-6.2.1.jar \
    meta \
    -o jaxrs-spec-streamingoutput \
    -n jaxrs-spec-streamingoutput \
    -p ${package}
```
(replace `${package}` with the actual package name)

From the generated module, only keep the generator class and the `CodegenConfig` in `META-INF/services`. Adapt the generator class as described in step 2 above.

---

The maven module can then be installed (`mvn install`) and used via the `openapi-generator-maven-plugin`. Set `generatorName` and include the maven module as plugin dependency:

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
   &lt;groupId&gt;org.openapitools&lt;/groupId&gt;
   &lt;artifactId&gt;openapi-generator-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
   &lt;version&gt;${plugin-version}&lt;/version&gt;
   &lt;executions&gt;
      &lt;execution&gt;
         &lt;phase&gt;generate-resources&lt;/phase&gt;
         &lt;goals&gt;...&lt;/goals&gt;
         &lt;configuration&gt;
            &lt;inputSpec&gt;...&lt;/inputSpec&gt;
            &lt;!-- 1. set generator name --&gt;
            &lt;generatorName&gt;jaxrs-spec-streamingoutput&lt;/generatorName&gt;
            &lt;configOptions&gt;...&lt;/configOptions&gt;
         &lt;/configuration&gt;
      &lt;/execution&gt;
   &lt;/executions&gt;
   &lt;dependencies&gt;
      &lt;dependency&gt;
         &lt;!-- 
            2. add this module to the dependencies
            e.g. &#39;${project.groupId}:api-codegen:${version}&#39;
         --&gt;
      &lt;/dependency&gt;
   &lt;/dependencies&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

The `configOptions` can be used as in [`jaxrs-spec` generator][5].


  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74940796/return-streamingoutput-from-interface-generated-by-openapi-spec-using-jaxrs-spec#comment132249915_74940796
  [2]: https://openapi-generator.tech/docs/plugins/#maven
  [3]: https://github.com/OpenAPITools/openapi-generator/blob/v6.2.1/modules/openapi-generator/src/main/java/org/openapitools/codegen/languages/JavaJAXRSSpecServerCodegen.java
  [4]: https://openapi-generator.tech/docs/usage/#meta
